			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ok the New idea is:
<br />
A short term single target Dot or Rain type spell ( we have both, but dots kinda unmage like).
<br />
Effect:
<br />
3 waves or ticks of a 600dd plus 2 sec stun. 4 sec cast time 450mana.
<br />

<br />
The benefits would be against casters and gaters that could be stunned. Alot of the trails and ldons have tons of these kinds of mobs and aside from the pet we dont have much chance to stop them.
<br />
The negetives are agro mostly it would need to be used at 50percent mob health especially if its a rain type spell.
<br />

<br />
Now for the Fix:
<br />
There has been several posts on how to fix the frenzied burnout AA but i dont believe this aspect has been covered.
<br />
Make frenzied burnout a passive ability. It simply makes your Burnout line of spells better. For example
<br />
These effects added to your regular burnout
<br />
10 percent overhaste
<br />
5 percent greater chance to crit
<br />
5 percent greater chance to flurry
<br />
100 dexterity
<br />
400 atk (or whatever amount would actually increase pets accuracy)
<br />

<br />
I think this sort of change would help the higher level pets increase their dps against the higher level targets where they have traditionally seen large drops to their dps.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
