				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><img src="images/smiles/eusa_shifty.gif" alt="Anxious" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I confess to have decent luck with rains.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />  1 or 2 casts in ten are triple resists, but most of them are single resist, and 2-3 per ten are triple hits.  I do sometimes get partial resists, but not often.  I mainly use rains (and used to use the DoT) in groups where I layered spells for maximum damage at a reasonable aggro level.  Used to use DoT, rain, nuke, rain, nuke in PoN while on horse, and it burned the mobs down pretty fast while not immediately dragging the thing onto me.  They do have some utility, but I agree that the 20% resist is a bit silly.  I'd accept 10%.<br />_________________<br />Dorai Darkspire, 65 Arch Convoker of Maelin Starpyre</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
